\doxysubsubsection{\texorpdfstring{PrintArrayLocation()}{PrintArrayLocation()}}
{\footnotesize\ttfamily void Print\+Array\+Location (\begin{DoxyParamCaption}\item[{const \mbox{\hyperlink{classLocation}{Location}}}]{array\+Locations\mbox{[}$\,$\mbox{]},  }\item[{int}]{n\+Locs }\end{DoxyParamCaption})}



Displays on the standard output an integer (the value in n\+Locs, number of locations in array\+Locations) and the content of the provided array of locations. Each location is displayed on a new line with the help of the \doxylink{classLocation_a8acfe3b137ecc53b8c4f33197ab63511}{Location\+::to\+String()} method. For example, here it is displayed an array with 4 locations\+: 4 24.\+8 14.\+9 Quadrangle 25.\+6 14.\+9 Ivy 26.\+4 14.\+9 Cottage 27.\+3 14.\+5 Cap \& Gown. 


\begin{DoxyParams}{Parameters}
{\em array\+Locations} & An array of \doxylink{classLocation}{Location} objects. Input parameter \\
\hline
{\em n\+Locs} & Number of \doxylink{classLocation}{Location} objects in the array array\+Locations. Input parameter\\
\hline
\end{DoxyParams}
